{"outcome":{"note":{}},"at":804558278.540359,"ticketId":"45","detail":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is my report:\n\n---\n\n## PLANNER REPORT — Issue #45: `chunkText` sentence-aware text chunker\n\n### 1. Project structure & conventions\n\n| Fact | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **Monorepo** | npm workspaces: `apps\/*` + `packages\/*` |\n| **App target** | `apps\/web` — SvelteKit app (Svelte 4 + Vite 5) |\n| **Utility location** | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/` — flat directory of `.ts` modules |\n| **Test location** | Co-located, same dir, `*.test.ts` suffix |\n| **Test framework** | **vitest** (v4), config at `apps\/web\/vitest.config.ts`, picks up `src\/**\/*.test.ts` |\n| **TypeScript** | Strict mode, `moduleResolution: \"bundler\"`, `type: \"module\"` in package.json |\n| **Export style** | Named exports (`export function foo()`), no `default` exports observed |\n| **File header** | JSDoc block describing purpose and design principles |\n| **Testing imports** | `import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';` |\n\n### 2. Where the code goes\n\n- **Module**: `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.ts` (new file)\n- **Tests**: `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.test.ts` (new file)\n\nThere is no existing `chunkText` definition anywhere in the repository (confirmed via `search_code`).\n\n### 3. Relevant existing code\n\n- **`apps\/web\/src\/lib\/synthesis\/constraints.ts:26–29`** — the current `normalizePreviewInput` function **truncates** over-long text with `.slice(0, maxInputChars)` — the lossy behavior this chunker is meant to replace\/supplement. The function uses `variant.maxInputChars` from the `VoiceVariant` type.\n\n- **`apps\/web\/src\/lib\/types.ts:2–13`** — `VoiceVariant` type includes `maxInputChars: number`.\n\n- **`apps\/web\/src\/lib\/language-utils.ts`** + `language-utils.test.ts` — model for the file structure, JSDoc style, import conventions, and test patterns to follow.\n\n### 4. What to build\n\nA pure exported function:\n\n```ts\nexport function chunkText(text: string, maxLength: number): string[]\n```\n\n**Semantics** (from the issue):\n1. Empty or whitespace-only → `[]`\n2. Input ≤ maxLength → `[text]`\n3. Split at sentence boundaries: `.`, `!`, `?` followed by whitespace (regex: `\/[.!?]\\s+\/`)\n4. Pack consecutive sentences until the next would exceed `maxLength`\n5. A single sentence > maxLength → hard-split into `maxLength`-sized pieces (no character loss)\n6. **Invariant**: no chunk's `.length > maxLength`\n7. **Invariant**: `chunks.join('')` preserves all non-whitespace content in order\n8. `maxLength <= 0` → throw a clear error\n\n**Test cases required** (minimum):\n- Empty input → `[]`\n- Whitespace-only input → `[]`\n- Input within limit → single-element array\n- Multi-sentence packing at boundaries\n- Over-long single sentence hard-split\n- No chunk exceeds maxLength\n- Content preservation (join equals original, modulo whitespace between sentences)\n- `maxLength <= 0` throws\n\n### 5. Verification commands\n\n- `npm run build:web` — runs `node scripts\/publish-catalog.mjs && npm run -w apps\/web build` (SvelteKit sync + Vite build)\n- `npm run test` — runs `npm --workspace apps\/web run test` which is `vitest run`\n\n### 6. Out of scope (confirmed from issue)\n\n- No wiring into dispatch\/synthesis\n- No provider-specific limit lookups\n- No language-specific segmentation beyond `.`, `!`, `?`\n\n---\n\n**Ready for the next phase.** No further investigation needed — the file conventions, test patterns, existing truncation behavior in `constraints.ts`, and all project tooling are fully characterized.","id":"45-99","phase":"planning"}
